                                <!-- Project Details Go Here -->
                                <h2 class="text-uppercase">Tips for saving money</h2>
                                <p class="item-intro text-muted">Make sure you have enough cash to enjoy yourself and for emergencies</p>
                                <p id="modalC">
                                    There are many, many different ways to save money- some of them are really easy, and beneficial to your life!
                                    Work costs you money!
                                    The UK average worker spends £160 on travel to work a month- you can reduce this by walking or cycling if you are lucky enough to live within a reasonable distance of your place of work.
                                    Lunches and snacks from nearby shops can also prove costly- when you are cooking in the evening, why not make a little extra and put it away in a tupperware box for lunch the next day?
                                    Don't forget to claim back your expenses! (Like travelling to work events, taking clients out for lunch etc.)<br />
                                    Buy things second hand! You can get some great, stylish clothes from places like charity shops. You can buy 2nd hand furniture in great condition from places like the British Heart Foundation. 2nd hand cars can save you a fortune!<br />
                                    Look for vouchers online before you make any purchases, or when you're deciding where to eat out for dinner.
                                </p>
                                <button class="btn btn-primary" data-dismiss="modal" type="button">
                                    <i class="fa fa-times"></i>
                                    Close
                                </button>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Modal 2 -->
    <div class="portfolio-modal modal fade" id="portfolioModal2" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-hidden="true">
        <div class="modal-dialog">
            <div class="modal-content" id="m2">
                <div class="close-modal" data-dismiss="modal">
                    <div class="lr">
                        <div class="rl"></div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="container">
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-lg-8 mx-auto">
                            <div class="modal-body" id="mb2">
                                <!-- Project Details Go Here -->
                                <h2 class="text-uppercase">Buying or Renting</h2>
                                <p class="item-intro text-muted">What are the pros and cons?</p>
                                <p id="modalC">
                                    When buying a property, you normally take out a <strong id="indpopOut1">
                                        mortgage.<span id="indhover1">
                                            An agreement, usually with a bank, where you pay a monthly amount for a property until you have met the total amount and then own the property!<br />
                                            Usually has a very low interest rate, so you will end up paying more for the house than buying it outright.
                                        </span>
                                    </strong>
                                    You usually need to make a large down payment to the bank, and then find a way of proving that you are trustworthy enough to pay them back (usually achieved using your <strong id="indpopOut2">
                                        credit rating
                                        <span id="indhover2">
                                            A value assigned to you which is basically how likely you are to pay your debts back.<br />
                                            It is mainly based on your ability pay off debts through your life.
                                        </span>
                                    </strong>).<br />
                                    This can prove difficult for many people, especially young people who are just beginning to find their way, so many people choose to <strong id="indpopOut3">
                                        rent<span id="indhover3">
                                            Paying a fixed rate to a landlord (who owns the property) in exchange for living there.
                                        </span>
                                    </strong> a property from a landlord.
                                    When you are renting, you are flexible to move around as you please. Landlords will make you sign a contract, but it will not be as long term as buying a property.
                                    The landlord is also responsible for paying for anything that isn't up to scratch in the house, like the dishwasher suddenly breaking.<br />
                                    Renting will also boost your credit rating a bit, as long as you create a history of on time rental payments!<br />

                                    Buying is seen as a better long term option however, as you are not paying rent to a landlord. Instead you are paying the mortgage, which will eventually lead to you owning the property and not having to worry about those monthly payments any more!
                                </p>
                                <button class="btn btn-primary" data-dismiss="modal" type="button">
                                    <i class="fa fa-times"></i>
                                    Close
                                </button>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Modal 3 -->
    <div class="portfolio-modal modal fade" id="portfolioModal3" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-hidden="true">
        <div class="modal-dialog">
            <div class="modal-content" id="m3">
                <div class="close-modal" data-dismiss="modal">
                    <div class="lr">
