                                <!-- Project Details Go Here -->
                                <h2 class="text-uppercase">Should I take out a payday loan?</h2>
                                <p class="item-intro text-muted">Warnings and advice</p>
                                <p id="modalC">
                                    If you are struggling for money, overdrawn and in need of some quick cash, you can take out a <strong id="indpopOut4">
                                        Payday loan.<span id="indhover4">
                                            This is a relatively small amount of money lent out at a high rate of interest on the agreement that you will repay over a specific amount of time.
                                        </span>
                                    </strong>
                                    You get the money instantly and you can withdraw the money on the same day. You can also apply online and it only takes a few minutes.

                                    However, the <strong id="indpopOut6">
                                        interest rate<span id="indhover6">
                                            This is the percentage you have to pay back on your debt. So if you borrow £1000, and the interest rate is 14% per month,
                                            then after one month you will now owe £1140!<br /> This can become a struggle to keep up with when borrowing large amounts!
                                        </span>
                                    </strong> is exceptionally high and some people have to take out another loan to pay off their first. This can lead to a vicious cycle of <strong id="indpopOut5">
                                        debt.
                                        <span id="indhover5">Simply, money that is owed to someone else!</span>
                                    </strong>
                                    They may also negatively impact your <strong id="indpopOut7">
                                        credit rating<span id="indhover7">
                                            A value assigned to you which is basically how likely you are to pay your debts back.<br />
                                            It is mainly based on your ability pay off debts through your life. It will affect your ability to borrow for cars/mortgages etc. for the rest of your life!
                                        </span>
                                    </strong>.<br />

                                    If you are going to take out one of these loans, be VERY careful and be sure you know exactly when and how you are going to pay the money back.<br />
                                    If you are lucky enough to have family or friends who can help, you could always go to them for help instead! If you do this, be very exact with them about when you are going to repay them and ensure that you do, or you will be in danger of losing their trust.
                                    (They will be unlikely to charge you interest!)

                                </p>
                                <button class="btn btn-primary" data-dismiss="modal" type="button">
                                    <i class="fa fa-times"></i>
                                    Close
                                </button>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Modal 5 -->
    <div class="portfolio-modal modal fade" id="portfolioModal5" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-hidden="true">
        <div class="modal-dialog">
            <div class="modal-content" id="m5">
                <div class="close-modal" data-dismiss="modal">
                    <div class="lr">
