                                <h2 class="text-uppercase">Getting a credit card</h2>
                                <p class="item-intro text-muted">Do you need one?</p>
                                <p id="modalC">
                                    There are many advantages and disadvantages of owning a credit card.
                                    While you do not need a <strong id="indpopOut8">
                                        credit card<span id="indhover8">
                                            Allows you to borrow money in small amounts when buying things. Usually the credit card company will give you about 30 days to pay this back before they start to charge interest- so be CAREFUL!<br />
                                            Depending on which company you use, the credit card can offer unique rewards if you manage them well by paying off the debt quickly!
                                        </span>
                                    </strong> to build your <strong id="indpopOut9">
                                        credit rating<span id="indhover9">
                                            A value assigned to you which is basically how likely you are to pay your debts back.<br />
                                            It is mainly based on your ability pay off debts through your life.
                                        </span>
                                    </strong>, it is very helpful if you can show that you pay off the card every month.
                                    However, owning a credit card and having a negative balance can impact your credit rating in a very bad way, so it is important to manage your credit card carefully.<br />
                                    Credit cards charge a high level of interest, which can lead to a lot of problems if you are unable to pay.
                                    A <strong id="indpopOut10">
                                        debit card<span id="indhover10">
                                            A card to draw money directly from your bank accounts. Usually needs a PIN to buy things worth over £30! 
                                        </span>
                                    </strong> will usually have an <strong id="indpopOut11">
                                        overdraft<span id="indhover11">
                                            A negative amount of money in your bank account- so you owe the bank this amount back.
                                        </span>
                                    </strong> you can go into, make sure you are fully aware of this before spending money that is not really yours!
                                    A debit card is a better way to control your money, and avoid paying high interest rates.
                                </p>
