                                <h2 class="text-uppercase">How much should you save from your wages?</h2>
                                <p class="item-intro text-muted">We've included a simple disposable income program for you!</p>
                                <p id="modalC">
                                    This question is of course totally up to you- you can save as much or as little as you'd like every month!
                                    That being said, it is always nice to have some extra money floating around, so saving at least some money every month is advisable.
                                    It may not seem important right now, but one day you will retire and have to live without earning any money at all!
                                    It depends on how much you earn, of course, but a good suggestion is to try and save 10% of your money each month.<br />
                                    This will allow you to occasionally splash out on holidays and luxury purchases (like a new car), as well as saving some money for when you are old and grey.
                                    Emergency money is always helpful to have as well in case any of your possessions suddenly break!<br />
                                    Getting married and raising a family isn't cheap- if you'd decide you would like to do this, you will likely have to start trying to save a little extra each month and put it aside.<br />

                                    Click on the link below to have a look at how much money you have to spare!
                                </p>
